						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">lidnariq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">How do you pick which palette to use?<br /></div><br /><br />For each pixel in the slice it finds the palette that has the closest color match, then whichever palette has the most matches &quot;wins&quot; that slice. I'm sure there must be better/more efficient algorithms.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Temporal dithering will dramatically improve the video quality, too. ( <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.pouet.net/prod.php?which=60939">http://www.pouet.net/prod.php?which=60939</a><!-- m --> )</div><br /><br />Awesome, I hadn't heard of that but I see some commercial LCD panels do it too. As I understand it, instead of shifting the error onto nearby pixels a la Floyd-Steinberg, you shift it onto the following frame?</div>

