						<div class="postbody">I've implemented temporal dithering in my image encoder, and it seems really flickery on my emulated output, but hopefully it'll look better on the NES. I may have to buy a PVM (good luck finding a consumer NTSC CRT in the UK), since I'm guessing that the crappy 240p deinterlacing my TV does will totally mangle it.<br /><br />Applying a motion blur effect in virtualdub makes it look great, so I guess my algorithm must be OK.</div>

